Yeltsin Appoints Kulik Deputy Prime Minister
MOSCOW , September 21 ( Xinhua ) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin Sunday appointed Gennady Kulik , vice chairman of the State Duma 's Budget Committee , deputy prime minister in charge of agriculture and food supplies .
Yeltsin announced the appointment when meeting with Prime Minister Yevgeny Primakov and Kulik in the Kremlin Monday morning , said the Itar-Tass news agency .
Kulik , of the Agrarian Party of Russia , said after the meeting that he advocated various forms of ownership , large agricultural cooperatives must exist alongside with private farms , and that farmers should be encouraged to work for profit .
Kulik said that there was no need now to import grain and the most pressing task now was to finish autumn harvest and prepare food for the winter .
Kulik was born in Novosokolnichesky of Pskov Region in 1935 .
He graduated from the Leningrad State University in 1957 .
In 1991 , Kulik became Vice-Chairman of the Council of Ministers and Minister for Agriculture and Food of the Russian Soviet Federal Socialist Republic of the former Soviet Union .
He was elected to the State Duma in 1993 , and since January 1996 has served as Vice Chairman of the Duma 's Committee for Budget , Taxes , Banks and Finance .
